<plot>Texas cattleman Opie Bedloe (Louis Cahhern) comes to Main to vist his son Joe (Van Johnson), a college instructor, and his wife Connie (Janet Leigh) in the hopes of persuading Joe to give up his teaching career and come back to Texas and take over the ranch. When Opie finds out that Connie, who is expecting a baby, can not afford the steaks she yearns for on Joe's salary, Opie, who believes that pregnant wimmen gotta have meat, arranges for the local butcher, Spangenberg (Walter Slezak) to cut his prices in half (with Opie paying the difference) so that Connie can have the meat she desires.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?113922</url></doc>
